e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">28
&amp; 29 November 2016 </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">Maison
des Sciences de l=E2=80=99Homme =E2=80=93 Grenoble =E2=80=93 France</span><=
/font></font></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">web
site: <a href=3D"http://hn2016en.condillac.org">hn2016en.condillac.org</a><=
/span></font></font></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">Deadline
for submission of abstracts: 2 June 2016</span></font></font></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">Notification
to authors: 21 July 2016 </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">The
international conference &quot;Digital Humanities and Iconography -
The case of alpine mural painting&quot;, to be held in Grenoble
(France) from 28 to 29 November 2016, is organised by the University
of Grenoble-Alpes (Maison des Sciences de l=E2=80=99Homme) and the
University of Savoie Mont Blanc (Condillac Research Group - LISTIC
lab). </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">As
part of the discussions conducted at the Maison des Sciences de
l=E2=80=99Homme Sciences-Alpes on the links between Digital Humanities and
Heritage, this international symposium, resolutely turned towards the
future, aims to debate one particular aspect: how to &quot;intelligently&qu=
ot;
access the data. How can digitised and scientifically validated data
in the field of Social Sciences and Humanities be made available to a
wider audience, that will not only share but also diversify its uses?
There will be two pivotal topics under discussion: on the one hand,
the need to respect the linguistic diversity involved in the
development and description of such data. On the other hand, the need
to consider the multiplicity of approaches that have presided over
the conceptual modelling of the data in question. </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">To
meet these objectives, without excluding other iconographic sources,
we draw the emphasis on case studies on the murals of the Alpine
regions from the thirteenth to the sixteenth centuries in the PREALP
database, hosted at the MSH-Alpes. </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">Three
areas have been selected: language - concepts - images. Particular
attention will be given to reflections on the contribution of
terminology to address the linguistic dimension, of ontology for the
conceptual dimension, and of image recognition for the selection and
classification of iconographic material. </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">This
conference is also an opportunity to establish an international
network of researchers to meet the challenges of a rapidly changing
field. </span></font></font>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify" lang=3D"e=
n-GB">
<br>
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0cm;line-height:100%" align=3D"justify"><font fac=
e=3D"Arial, serif"><font style=3D"font-size:10pt" size=3D"2"><span lang=3D"=
en-GB">Paper
proposals (800 words maximum), in French, English or Italian, which
will be the three working languages of the conference, should be sent
to the organising committee:</span></font></font></p>
